In anticipation of Human Rights Day on December 10th, the author calls for the release of political prisoners in Cuba who were detained after the July 11, 2021 protests. The protestors demonstrated their fundamental freedoms, such as freedom of expression and peaceful assembly, despite facing oppression. The United States supports the Cuban people in their fight for human rights and their involvement in shaping Cuba's future. The author pledges to continue advocating for the release of all those imprisoned during the crackdown and holding Cuban officials accountable for violence against peaceful protests.